RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO $2,800 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG TICKET pressed the pace while three wide, was moving up to duel shortly leaving the turn, took charge in the early stretch to kick clear under a strong drive prevailing in the end. FIND NEW ROADS bumped foe at the start, then chased the pace while two wide, bid on the turn to rally in the early stretch and was closing well and was up for the place prize. WINGS FOR ENO lead the way into the turn while two wide, was challenged for the lead by an outer rival heading into the stretch, dug in gamely but could not retain bid and gave way in the end. GOLD DECLARATION raced behind the field while two wide, was gaining throughout the turn while four wide to close well in the stretch but it was not enough. NEVER OVER ME was bumped at the start, then stalked the pace from the inside, settled back throughout the turn to rebid again in the stretch but came up empty in the end. TWELVE PACK chased the pace while five wide, bid from the three path on the turn then flattened out in the stretch. BRILLIANT COLORS settled behind the field along the inside and failed to menace. GREYSTOKE bid for the lead early between rivals then dropped back and had no final bid in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 96. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE APRIL 22, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22, 2023 A llowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 22, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EASTER SNAP pressed the pace for a half mile, took command two wide entering the far turn, opened an advantage turning for home and held well in the drive to the wire under strong urging. VIOLIN MAKER taken in hand to settle in the clear down the backside, started a long rally leaving the three-eighths pole, rallied four wide and closed well to gain the place. FLIP THE COIN JAN checked off the leaders heels into the first turn, settled into an inside tracking position to the far turn, waited for racing room at the top of the lane and finished up gamely along the fence to be coming late. MISHKO stalked the leaders from three wide, loomed up boldly turning for home and was outfinished late. HOLY EMPEROR broke sharp to take the lead from the gate, dropped to the rail into the first turn impeding FLIP THE COIN JAN, raced on the lead in a duel to the far turn and faded into the stretch. F J'S GEM raced evenly while never posing a threat. CONVICTION TRADE trailed throughout as a non-factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPITS KASH dueled for the lead from the inside throughout the first three quarters of the course, then kicked clear in the stretch and held sway till the end. COWBOY RIDGE stalked the pace while three wide, was gaining on the far turn to confront the dueling leaders in the stretch, gained to place position in late stretch but was out bid in the end and was best for third. MOROLICIOUS saved ground while racing down the backstretch along the inside and into the turn, then rallied in the early stretch to close with willingness in the end. TEXAS HOLDEM chased the pace from the inside down the backstretch and into the far turn to rally in the early stretch but came up evenly in the end. FANDO chased the pace while two wide, then menaced on the far turn from the three path but came up evenly in the stretch. PHARME'S PHAITH veered out at the start, then raced in the four path down the backstretch, bid on the turn into the stretch and was no threat. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 10 1M Turf CR: 105. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 36500. (PLUS UP TO $7,300 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL SINCE OCTOBER 22, 2022 OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Sinc e January 22, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 22, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances). (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on th e main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINGAPORE FLASH prominent early, moved up to press the pace from between horses down the backstretch, moved with CARLEA'S DREAM to take a short lead in upper stretch, came out to bump that one midway in the lane when hit left-handed impeding his forward momentum momentarily, opened a short lead and held off the late closer. CAIRO WARRIOR tracked the pacesetters to the far turn, rallied four wide down the lane and closed with a rush to be up for the place. CARLEA'S DREAM stalked the leaders from three wide down the backside, moved with the winner to duel on the lead turning for home, was bumped midway in the stretch when the winner ducked out briefly, was knocked off-stride, re-gathered momentum and finished gamely. LOGICAL MYTH reserved near the rear of the field for a half mile, was forced to travel wide throughout and made late gains in the stretch. GO SPEED RACER GO raced between horses in striking position to the head of the stretch and failed to sustain a bid. U S NAVY CROSS trailed for most of the way and passed tiring rivals in the lane. TATANKA sped to an early clear lead, dropped back when challenged and tired. TRULY DANZIG never seriously threatened. THERE WAS A STEWARDS INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN, UPON REVIEW OF THE REPLAY, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT THE WINNER INTERFERED WITH THE THIRD PLACE FINISHER AND THE WINNER WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED THIRD.
